schedule.show_name: Explore the landscapes and wildlife of Mexico, where deserts meet tropics, including footage of fledgling pygmy owls, orca hunting, new species in flooded caves, and orchid bees.
A look at the diverse continent of South America, where a pod of killer whales snatch baby seals right under their mothers' noses, and a jaguar hunts caimans in the jungle.
The filmmaker sheds light on the behaviour and physical features of major African predators and the strategies that they use to kill their prey and defend themselves.
Parenting in the ocean demands dedication and intelligence. From navigating the reef, to teaching young to hunt giants, these parents have remarkable strategies.
Surviving the vast mountains of Italy, the chamois are an endemic group of species that are facing a series threat of extinction.
A nasty cub attempts to mate with members of the pride, for which it is asked to leave the group by an authoritative adult through the use of violence.
Along the eastern coasts of Australia, lies a tropical haven that offers refuge for a wide range of fauna that lives exclusively there.
Tanzania's towering northern mountains, formed by ancient volcanoes, provide diverse habitats and hold water in its great centerpiece even during the driest times.
Take a look at an unusual duel between a boomslang and a chameleon on the tar road in the Kruger National Park in South Africa along with Dianne Tipping-Wood.
Spanish juniper woods are some of the most distinctive in the world. Each tree has its own unique shape and the woodlands are adapted to cold and dry climates.
To master the art of disguise for many is an impossible feat but for creatures like octopuses and chameleons, it is a powerful weapon that makes them experts at hunting and hiding.
Table Mountain National Park in South Africa is home to a diverse range of plants and animals that belong to the rich ocean and the windswept coast.
Animals in the wild are in a continuous fight to ensure their survival. Find out the reasons that lead to these dangerous disputes.
A hyena and a warthog family learn to cohabilate by helping each other by keeping an eye on threatening predators that threaten their survival.
The plains and woodlands of the Luangwa Valley are the wildest and most merciless of all neighbourhoods where duels between predator and prey are played out both day and night.
In South Africa's Greater Kruger Park, the filmmaker follows Chinga, the little lioness, who needs to pay close attention to her parents to survive in an unforgiving wild kingdom.
The Royals, an elephant family, struggle to survive in the face of a landscape turning to dust while wild dog matriarch Phoenix introduces five new puppies to the pack.
The filmmaker sheds light on the turbulent lives of hippopotamuses where they fight for dominance with each other while maintaining a symbiotic relationship with crocodiles.
Tanzania's towering northern mountains, formed by ancient volcanoes, provide diverse habitats and hold water in its great centerpiece even during the driest times.
Numerous animals adapt through a series of small mutations in order to compete more effectively in the game of evolution.
The leopard is perhaps the best-equipped big cat with a population spread far and wide, but lions have almost no predators.
The filmmaker offers detailed insights into the activities of leopards thriving in their natural habitats of the Yala National Park in Sri Lanka.
In the Wild West, rattlesnakes emerge in the hundreds, woodpeckers compete to store food, bison battle on the Great Plains and cranes gather in vast numbers on their age-old migration.
At Amazon, giant otters hunt together while black caimans prey on newly hatched turtles. Meanwhile, a harpy eagle chick experiences its first days and army ants on the move reveal new behaviours.
Mobius Foundation: Embers of Hope
Mobius Foundation: Embers of Hope
The filmmaker follows the journey of two female cheetahs in the Serengeti as they struggle to raise their young cubs and protect their families from predators and starvation.
Parents must constantly balance risk and reward when raising young in open grasslands that promise plentiful food and places to call home.
Explore the life of a family of brown bears in a year, the special characteristics of the rutting season of Roe Deer in the Mountains of Central Italy, and the migration of salamanders in autumn.
On Botswana's Linyanti Plains, three cheetah brothers, Achilles, Odin and Shiva fiercely guard their territory. But when Achilles unexpectedly dies, the others must learn to defend against invaders.
At Amazon, giant otters hunt together while black caimans prey on newly hatched turtles. Meanwhile, a harpy eagle chick experiences its first days and army ants on the move reveal new behaviours.
